title.label: Not formatted for iPhone X and up

content.label: iPhone X does not have a home screen button. Instead, it has a little bar at the bottom of the touch screen that you can swipe up to act like the old home screen button. The problem with this is that Where’s My Water is formatted to use the very very bottom and sides of the screen. There are some levels of the game that require pressing down so low on the screen, that game play stops because the iPhone and game think you are trying to press the home screen button/swipe the bar. This really really needs to be fixed to make game play more enjoyable.

title.label: Just another poorly designed money grab by people who don’t test the game.

content.label: The levels are okay, usually. The buttons respond, sometimes. Then there’s this weird part at the end of the second set of levels that says you either have to pay or watch 3 videos over 3 days to move on, even if you have all of the ducks from before. This game comes across as a money grab by the developers. They are constantly making you watch ads and the only way to get tools is to watch an ad or buy them. Many of the levels are either painfully easy or so hard that they make you want to delete the game right then and there.
